docs.snippet: The American economy added 151,000 jobs last month, a performance that could support the position of those within the Fed who favor delaying an interest-rate increase....
docs.lead_paragraph: The American economy added 151,000 jobs last month, a performance that could support the position of those within the Fed who favor delaying an interest-rate increase.
docs.abstract: Labor Dept reports data for August shows 151,000 jobs were added, unemployment remained at 4.9 percent and wage gains were modest; economists interpret results as sign economy is doing well but not overheating and interest rate hike unnecessary.

headline.main: Slower Growth in Jobs Report May Give Fed Pause on Interest Rates
headline.print_headline: Slower Jobs Growth May Give Fed Pause on Rates

byline.contributor: Alan Rappeport contributed to this article.
